{"type":"message","id":"afc1e5e5","parentId":"c58c5321","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:00:29.845Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lt48s5f7slhc_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 1221\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 080016 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs. variant patterns across pulse logs. The pulse logs exist in `logs/pulse_*.md` format. I need to build the classifier to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy.\r\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"cool-meadow","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 1221\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 080016 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs. variant patterns across pulse logs. The pulse logs exist in `logs/pulse_*.md` format. I need to build the classifier to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353629843}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd7bc957","parentId":"afc1e5e5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:00:29.850Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lt48s5f7slhc_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 075914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/TIC/experiment.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 complete\r\n- Key insight: Compression and Causal Discovery are the SAME problem (COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY)\r\n- Next action: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Pending: Measure compression ratio, implement TIC classifier\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to implement the TIC classifier on pulse logs. Let me look at what pulse logs exist and start implementing.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n6. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most immediate and concrete action seems to be implementing the TIC classifier. Let me check what pulse logs exist and create a basic TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me first look at the existing pulse log to understand the format, then implement a simple TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next critical step, but first I need to understand the structure of pulse logs to implement the classifier. The last pulse log `pulse_2026-03-24 075816.md` should reveal the format.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine the most recent pulse log to understand its structure, then create a basic TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier that can identify invariant vs. variant elements across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Concept\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. Elements that persist across pulses are causal.\r\nElements that change are effects or noise.\r\n\r\n## Algorithm\r\n1. Extract key elements (goals, insights, pending actions) from pulse logs\r\n2. Compare element frequency across last N pulses\r\n3. Classify: invariant (persistent) vs. variant (changing)\r\n4. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\n## Classification Rules\r\n- **INVARIANT**: Appears in 70%+ of analyzed pulses\r\n- **VARIANT**: Appears in <70% of analyzed pulses\r\n- **EMERGING**: New element appearing in last 2 pulses\r\n- **DECAYING**: Element that appeared but hasn't appeared in last 3 pulses\r\n\r\n## Implementation Status\r\n- [ ] Parse pulse logs for structured elements\r\n- [ ] Build element frequency matrix\r\n- [ ] Apply classification thresholds\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\nfile: src/TIC/classifier.py\r\n```\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment Results\r\n\r\n## Experiment Date: 2026-03-24\r\n## Status: PENDING\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n- Analyze last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Extract: goals, insights, pending actions, observations\r\n- Classify each element as invariant/variant\r\n- Predict next pulse from invariant set\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Classification accuracy: >70%\r\n- Next-pulse prediction: >60%\r\n\r\n## Results\r\n(TBD - run TIC classifier)\r\n\r\n## Analysis\r\n(TBD)\r\nfile: experiments/TIC/EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 07:59:33\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774353629848}}
